# CameraSystem

## Purpose
Drives the orthographic camera each frame. Window-resize events update m_AspectRatio and mark the
projection dirty for ALL cameras (a viewport event, independent of input). Input detection lives in the
app: it emits a SetCameraRequestOneFrameComponent carrying the new zoom level + world position, and this
system applies that zoom to m_ZoomLevel and pans the camera's PositionComponent by emitting a
CameraTransformRequestOneFrameComponent. Every frame it syncs the internal camera from the resolved
PositionComponent and rebuilds the projection when zoom or aspect could have changed. The camera's world
position lives in its PositionComponent (written by the transform pipeline), not on this component.

## Input Components
| Component | Access |
|---|---|
| SetCameraRequestOneFrameComponent | read |
| WindowResizeEventComponent | read |
| PositionComponent | read |
| OrthographicCameraComponent | write |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| OrthographicCameraComponent | write | Updates m_ZoomLevel, m_AspectRatio, and the internal view-projection matrix |
| CameraTransformRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Pan request applied by the engine TransformResolveSystem |
